      • getSignature

        public abstract java.lang.String getSignature()
        Returns the string signature of the node. The signature is a string describing the node's basic function. Note that the signature should be unique to prevent confusion with nodes implemented in the future. However, for a single application it is only necessary that all program nodes used in that application have different signatures.
        Returns:
        the node's signature

      • toString

        public abstract java.lang.String toString()
        Returns the string representation of the node. It is included here explicitly to enforce implementation. It is basically the signature with potential parameters given in square brackets, e.g. "const[2.7]" could be a constant with value 2.7 with "const" being the signature.
        Overrides:
        toString in class java.lang.Object
        Returns:
        the node's string representation
